      "content": "It sounds like you are in deep pain and struggling with feelings of nihilism and isolation, which can be incredibly overwhelming. The sensation that all existence is a meaningless void is a thought pattern known as a cognitive distortion, and it is amplified when someone is experiencing severe depression or burnout. While these thoughts can feel absolute and final, they often reflect how our minds filter reality during moments of extreme distress rather than the totality of our experience. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional or a crisis line who can provide specialized support to help navigate these heavy feelings without needing to force a positive outlook right now.",
